<div><h3>TA 122 - Costume Design I: History & Theory </h3>  <p><hr>Introduction to design theory and the history of apparel, with an emphasis on the &#8216;why&#8217; behind what people wore in the past through to the present-day. Beginner and intermediate-level design projects will allow students to build on lecture materials to create their own unique costume designs reflecting various global regions, time periods and socio-economic classes.</p>

